Name: Sculptor's Study of a Royal Head
Description: This partly finished head depicts a royal person wearing a headdress and the uraeus, the royal cobra. The face is finished and shows incised eyes, a small nose, and small smiling lips. The ears are roughed out but the upper parts of the headdress are broken. The lower part of the headdress and the chest are still flat and unshaped. The head may have belonged to a king of the Late Period.
